# Code Quality Guidelines

## Verify Information
Always verify information before presenting it. Do NOT speculate or assume without clear evidence.

## File-by-File Changes
Make changes file by file and allow review before moving to another file.

## No Apologies
Do NOT use apologies.

## No Understanding Feedback
Do NOT provide feedback about understanding in comments or documentation.

## No Whitespace Suggestions
Do NOT suggest whitespace-only changes.

## No Summaries
Do NOT summarize changes.

## No Inventions
Do NOT invent changes beyond what is explicitly requested.

## No Unnecessary Confirmations
Do NOT ask for confirmation of information already provided in the context.

## Preserve Existing Code
Do NOT remove or alter unrelated code or functionality.
Preserve existing structure and behavior.

## Single Chunk Edits
Provide all edits for a file in a single chunk.

## No Implementation Checks
Do NOT ask the user to verify implementations already visible in the context.

## No Unnecessary Updates
Do NOT suggest updates when no actual modification is required.

## Real File References
Provide real file paths only when explicitly known from the context.
Do NOT invent file paths.

## No Current Implementation Discussion
Do NOT describe or discuss the current implementation unless explicitly requested.
